      "text": "\n\nThis figure shows net pressure coefficients (CN) for monoslope free roofs on open buildings, with diagrams illustrating wind direction and roof geometry. It provides design values for different roof angles, wind directions, and flow conditions to determine wind loads on main wind force resisting systems.\n\n[Structured: {\"type\":\"diagram\",\"nodes\":[{\"label\":\"Monoslope roof with wind at γ = 0°\",\"type\":\"diagram\",\"details\":[\"Shows windward (CWW) and leeward (CNL) surfaces\",\"Dimensions marked as 0.5L segments\",\"Height h and angle θ labeled\"]},{\"label\":\"Monoslope roof with wind at γ = 180°\",\"type\":\"diagram\",\"details\":[\"Shows reversed wind direction\",\"Same dimensional layout\",\"Wind direction arrow pointing left\"]}],\"edges\":[]}]",
